the position of Kai, appears in Keiko's classroom and declares that
Keiko's scientific teachings about the wormmhole are in conflict with
Bajoran beliefs. Winn's announcement divides the Federation officers
and Bajorans on the station who follow Winn. Sisko attempts to enlist
the aid of Vedek Bareil, the quiet leader in the race to become Kai,
but initially meets with no cooperation. When terrorist acts begin, it
becomes apparent that Bajoran political interests may also be deeply
involved - and the Federation crew of Deep Space 9 may have outstayed
their welcome.


