A Bajoran man arrives on DS9 with his adopted son, a young
Cardassian who was abandoned when his people withdrew from
Bajor. This draws the attention of the Cardassian government,
particularly Gul Dukat, who claims he is eager to solve the
dilemma of Cardassian war orphans left behind on Bajor. DS9's
resident tailor, Garak, seems to find Dukat's sudden pledge to
resolve the abandoned children's situation ironic, since the
boy in question is really the son of one of the civilian assembly
who voted to pull the Cardassian military out of Bajoran space -
one of Dukat's political adversaries. Sisko and Dr. Bashir, aided
and abetted by Garak's cryptic advice, must decide the fate of 
the Cardassian youth, possibly deciding the end result of an
internal power struggle whose combatants couldn't care less
about the boy's situation.


