@Node DS974 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/DS9/The Visitor"

  @{b}The Visitor@{ub}

It's several decades in the future. Jake Sisko is an old man, living in his
grandfather's house on the Louisiana bayou. On a rainy night, a visitor
arrives - a young woman who aspires to be writer. Jake tells her the story of
why he hasn't written in years. Long ago, he was on a trip with his father in
the Defiant when an accident in the engine room caused his father to disappear
before his eyes. Yet when Ben Sisko began appearing to him in the flesh, for a
few minutes at a time, with years between appearances, it became clear that he
was not dead, but trapped in subspace. Jake went on with his life, married,
became a famous writer - but was forever haunted by his fathers's disappearance,
and became obsessed with rescuing him. Now, Jake has finally found a solution...
but what will it cost him?


