@Node DS9172 "STCCG.guide/Episodes/DS9/Extreme Measures"

  @{b}Extreme Measures@{ub}

When Kira brings a terminally ill Odo back to the station for medical
treatment, he orders her to leave him and return to help the Cardassian
Resistance. Later, O'Brien and Bashir inform Sisko of their plan to lure
a Section 31 operative, who may hold the cure to Odo's disease, to the
station. The scheme works when Sloan, the director of the unscanctioned
Starfleet extremist organization that infected Odo - as part of a genocidal
plot against his people - arrives. But when Bashir places a Romulan mind
probe on the agent, who refuses to give information regarding a cure, Sloan
attempts suicide in the science lab by activating a neuro-depolarizing
device in his brain.


